<br>
As I set out, my primary goal was to locate the hidden city of the Coldain, so I missed a number of /locs (mainly zone lines). But I did record a fair number of interesting places along the way that can be explored with greater numbers. Here are some landmarks I noted along the way.<br>
<br>
***WARNING***<br>
The below report is full of spoilers. Don't read if you want to find stuff out on your own.<br>
<br>
The raft out to the gnomish ice cutter is in the desert of North Ro. There is a gnomish pirate there who guards the dock. This dock is usable by all races and religions.<br>
<br>
The Iceclad Ocean is enormous. It feels like you sail forever before you get to a gnomish pirate outpost. This outpost is small, but is a good place for supplies and a launching point. There is a useable druid ring in the area, but I was unable to find it due to the heavy snow falling. ***WARNING*** Wolf form is kill on sight to the gnome pirates. I watched four druids die as they all diembarked and cast wolf form at the same time.<br>
<br>
Heading west, you'll do some glacier hopping. Gnolls, frost giants and an interesting Shadow Tower (when you hear the loud beating heart, you are nearing the tower... a very spooky experience). Everything I saw coned from 30 to 35. Continue west and you will see the largest bridge ever (makes the North Karana bridges seem like child's toys). This is the crossing to the Eastern Wastes.<br>
<br>
I pretty much went on a hunch and continued due west from the bridge. After awhile, I saw a plume of smoke on the horizon. I encountered a small camp of Coldain warriors (apprehensive, but protective) before I reached the plume. As I crested a ridge west of the camp, a large fort came into view (-3467, 771). According to the Coldain, this fort once belonged to them but has been overrun by orcs. I later discovered that it sits on top of a series of beautiful caverns (Crystal Caverns) that can be accessed from a crystal located in the back of the fort.<br>
<br>
Still seeking the Coldain city, I continued westward. I encountered a frost giant fort (-2370, 3271) along the way. Be very wary of your footing in this area. The hills can be very steep and canyons can appear out of no where if you're not paying attention.<br>
<br>
I eventually came upon a canyon pass that lead me to the Great Divide. Still continuing west, I discovered a set of wizard spires (-1801, -2772) and another giant fort (-2543, -2582) that seemed much better guarded than the previous fort. Be wary of the canyon where the wizard spires are ad frost giants seem to patrol right through the spires.<br>
<br>
Continuing westward, I came across a light stream. Following the stream to the left leads you to a cavern full of wurms of every type (-3083, -265). Following the stream to the right leads you to a beautiful waterfall (-40, -112). But every good explorer knows to check behind the waterfall for passageways. Sure enough, a hidden entrance there leads into the Coldain City of Thurgadin.<br>
<br>
The city is set up underground and features some very unique and beautiful architecture. The Coldain were apprehensive, but not hostile. They are very talkative and social if you find the right spots. I found no less than three taverns (one was absolutely huge). There seems to be just about everything you would normally find in a city safehaven. There was a bank (-343, 165) and vendors for every trade skill (although I couldn't find any alchemy supplies). I did locate a rogue guildmaster though (13, -120).<br>
<br>
After exploring for a while, I located what I believe to be the ruling house of the Coldain, Icewell Keep (184, 2).<br>
<br>
Be advised that there are some hostile creatures in the mines of the Coldain (60, -193) and in Icewell Keep.<br>
<br>
