<br>
- I highly recommend caution when fighting things here. Faction is going to be very important in determining where is a safehaven and where is not. Just because it's a giant or dragon doesn't mean you should kill it.<br>
<br>
- There is a bridge just inside the entrance to the Coldain city that is covered with ice and involves a rather long fall. Use caution.<br>
<br>
- Item drops are a bit odd, and in some cases don't even exist. If you are coming to Velious looking for loot, don't be disappointed if you don't get anything.<br>
<br>
- Be alert for traps in dungeons. The most popular trap at this time seems to be pit traps.<br>
<br>
- As I mentioned, there are some rather steep hills and canyons in the Eastern Wastes. If you ae zooming around with SoW or SoS, you stand a good chance of taking 10K+ damage from falls.<br>
<br>
- If you are a melee character and plan on extended adventuring, head directly to the Coldain city for a bind before doing anything else.<br>
<br>
- Be wary of clicking on unknown objects. You never know if they are going to be one way teleports someplace <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
